{"word":"φρενόω","slug":"φρενόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φρενόω</b></el> <el>(φρενόω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ώσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φρήν'><el>φρήν</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to make wise, instruct, inform, teach</i>, <el>τινά</el> <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; <el>φρενώσω δ' οὐκέτ' ἐξ αἰνιγμάτων</el>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>will teach</i> plainly, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be elated</i>, <b><a href='S:Babrius'>Babr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}